### Also in This Update — v0.3.x (ApplicationV2 Migration)

The module was migrated from the deprecated Foundry `Application` base class to `ApplicationV2` + `HandlebarsApplicationMixin`. This resolves the deprecation warning introduced in Foundry v13 and ensures forward compatibility through v16 and beyond. The migration was internal — no change to the module's behaviour or appearance.

Key technical changes:
- `static DEFAULT_OPTIONS` replaces `static defaultOptions`
- `_prepareContext()` replaces `getData()`
- `_onRender()` replaces `activateListeners()` — plain DOM, no jQuery
- All dialogs updated from `Dialog` to `DialogV2`
- `getSceneControlButtons` hook handles both the v13+ object shape and the older array shape for backwards compatibility

